:: Home Orphan Rebellious Prank 3
<<effects>>
<<npc Bailey 3>><<person3>>

<<if $phase is 1>> /* Offer to help them set up */
	You help the orphans set up the classic "bucket over the door" prank. When finished, you hide behind the nearest door, leaving a gap wide enough for the three of you to peer out. <<= playerBellyVisible() ? "Your belly is awkward, but you" : "You">> squeeze together so you're all able to see.
	<br><br>
	When Bailey starts approaching <<his>> office,
	<<if $orphan_hope gte 40>>
		you know the orphans are excited, but they do their best to hold it in.
	<<elseif $orphan_hope gte 10>>
		the orphans are noticeably excited, and you see them eyeing each other conspicuously. You attempt to get their attention and calm them down. <<gstress>><<stress 6>>
	<<else>>
		the orphans are obviously restless. You hope they don't draw attention. <<ggstress>><<stress 12>>
	<</if>>
<<else>> /* Offer to cover for them */
	You wait nearby Bailey's office as you keep an eye out, trying to look casual. Before the other orphans can finish, you spot Bailey rounding a corner and swiftly intercept <<him>>.
	<br><br>
	<<if $speech_attitude is "meek">>
		"P-pardon me..." You timidly get Bailey's attention. "I had a question—i-if you have the time...?"
		<br><br>
		Bailey gives you an irritated look, but <<he>> stops, and turns away from the direction of <<his>> office.
		<br><br>
		"What is it?" <<He>> crosses <<his>> arms.
		<br><br>
		You shrink a little under <<his>> scrutiny. "It's just... I've been paying you for some time now, and I wanted to know how much left I have to pay off...?"
	<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
		"Hey!" You brashly stride over to Bailey. "I'd like to lodge a complaint."
		<br><br>
		Bailey gives you an irritated look, but <<he>> stops, and turns away from the direction of <<his>> office.
		<br><br>
		"I'm sure you would," <<he>> grumbles. <<He>> crosses <<his>> arms. "What is it, then?"
		<br><br>
		"You've been making me pay you off for my 'care' for a while now." You mirror <<his>> stance, undaunted. "Where's all that money going exactly? Because it sure doesn't feel like it's going back into the orphanage."
	<<else>>
		"Excuse me." You wave at Bailey to get <<his>> attention as you approach. "I just wanted to double check with you how much you're expecting me to pay you this week."
		<br><br>
		Bailey gives you an irritated look, but <<he>> stops, and turns away from the direction of <<his>> office.
		<br><br>
		Bailey scoffs and crosses <<his>> arms. "You owe me <<printmoney $rentmoney>>."
		<<if $baileydefeatedchain gte 2>>
			<<He>> glares at you. "I'm not going easy on you this time if you continue to be uncooperative."
		<<elseif $baileydefeatedchain is 1>>
			<<He>> squints at you. "You'd better actually pay up this time."
		<<else>>
			<<He>> raises an eyebrow. "You'd better have it by <<rentday>>."
		<</if>>
		<br><br>
		<<if $money gte $rentmoney>>
			"I should be able to,"
		<<else>>
			"I'll do my best,"
		<</if>>
		you reply noncommittally. "Will I ever learn how much more I owe you?"
	<</if>>
	<br><br>
	Bailey fails to notice <span class="green">the orphans sneaking out of <<his>> office behind <<him>>.</span> <<He>> sneers condescendingly. "Wouldn't you like to know?" Without answering your question, <<he>> turns and heads for <<his>> office. You find the two orphans, stifling giggles.
<</if>>
<br><br>

